meta {
  name: POST pretripclimate start (NA-specific climatisation start)
  type: http
  seq: 8
}

post {
  url: https://b-h-s.spr.{{country}}00.p.con-veh.net/ev/v1/vehicle/{{vehicle_uuid}}/pretripclimate/start
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

body:json {
  {}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
  User-Agent: MyVW/1.0 Android
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 (Group C). VW North America climatisation start endpoint.

  NA uses the explicit ``/pretripclimate/start`` path name, distinct
  from the EU CARIAD-BFF naming ``/climatisation/start``. Same Cox
  ``/ev/v1/vehicle/{uuid}/...`` prefix as the rest of the NA stack.

  Companion endpoints (same shape, different suffix):

  - ``POST /ev/v1/vehicle/{uuid}/pretripclimate/stop``
  - ``POST /ev/v1/vehicle/{uuid}/pretripclimate/windowheating/start``
  - ``POST /ev/v1/vehicle/{uuid}/pretripclimate/windowheating/stop``

  NA-specific shape vs EU:

  - EU CARIAD-BFF: ``POST /vehicle/v1/vehicles/{vin}/climatisation/start``
  - EU also accepts a rich payload (climate mode, per-seat heating,
    window heating flags). NA expects an empty body for the
    pretripclimate start; settings are configured separately via
    ``POST /ev/v1/vehicle/{uuid}/pretripclimate/settings``.

  A/B fallback contract: the Python implementation tries the NA path
  first and falls back to ``/ev/v1/vehicle/{uuid}/climatisation/start``
  on a 404, so older Cox firmware that only knew the EU-style alias
  keeps working without user intervention.
}
